        @NonNull
public final LogParameters.Builder sessionHistorySize(int aHistorySize)

        The number of sessions that will be kept in history along with their starting time. This is used for Locuaz logs that come in late after the session has ended.

        By default, this will be set to 5 if no value is provided.

        Parameters:

      • maxStoredDialogLogs

        @NonNull
public final LogParameters.Builder maxStoredDialogLogs(int maxNumber)

        The maximum number of dialog logs (not including dialog alarms) that will be stored in the logging directory before they are no longer saved. If space is made available by time the next logging session starts, then logs will continue to be saved.

        If a value less than or equal to 0 is given, then no limit is imposed on the number of logs that can be saved.

        Parameters:
        maxNumber - The maximum number of dialog logs to save into the logging directory.
        Returns:
        This instance.

      • maxStoredAsrLogs

        @NonNull
public final LogParameters.Builder maxStoredAsrLogs(int maxNumber)

        The maximum number of ASR logs that will be stored in the logging directory before they are no longer saved. If space is made available by time the next logging session, starts, then the logs will continue to be saved.

        If a value less than or equal to 0 is given, then no limit is imposed on the number of logs that can be saved.

        Note: An ASR log consists of a WAV file and a corresponding XML file. Therefore, if this value is set to 100, then it means that the maximum number of files that will be saved is 100 WAV files and 100 XML files for a total of 200 files (since each ASR log is a pair).

        Parameters:
        maxNumber - The maximum number of ASR logs to store.
        Returns:
        This instance.
